1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:02,170
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:02,240 --> 00:00:03,680
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,680 --> 00:00:04,980
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:58,760
I'm sorry.
The patient has passed away.

5
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:02,600
No. You can still save her.

6
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:05,770
My sister isn't one
to give up so easily.

7
00:01:06,140 --> 00:01:07,140
Myung Hui.

8
00:01:08,170 --> 00:01:10,640
Myung Hui, you told me.

9
00:01:11,940 --> 00:01:14,550
You said you'd do what it takes
to live, until the very end.

10
00:01:14,810 --> 00:01:18,020
Myung Hui!

11
00:01:18,450 --> 00:01:21,120
Myung Hui, come on. Breathe.

12
00:01:21,690 --> 00:01:23,660
Myung Hui, please.

13
00:01:30,730 --> 00:01:31,730
The baby's alive.

14
00:01:36,530 --> 00:01:37,770
The baby's alive!

15
00:01:40,570 --> 00:01:41,740
The baby's alive.

16
00:01:42,070 --> 00:01:43,810
The baby might have a chance
if we operate now.

17
00:01:45,540 --> 00:01:48,310
The oxygen supply was likely cut off
when the mother passed away.

18
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:52,020
If the baby has brain damage,
it will require additional care.

19
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:53,750
She needs to be moved
to a larger hospital...

20
00:01:53,820 --> 00:01:56,190
The nearest one is an hour away.

21
00:01:57,590 --> 00:01:59,020
This baby...

22
00:01:59,260 --> 00:02:00,960
and you as well...

23
00:02:02,230 --> 00:02:04,130
I love you both so much...

24
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:07,970
that I'll do anything
to protect you.

25
00:02:15,770 --> 00:02:18,280
If we wait any longer,
the baby will die too.

26
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:22,950
That baby was her whole world.
I can't let it die.

27
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:27,090
Please do the operation.

28
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:31,160
There's still a chance
for a miracle.

29
00:02:37,660 --> 00:02:38,700
Doctor, please.

30
00:02:44,370 --> 00:02:46,870
- No...
- The delivery room is already in use,

31
00:02:47,140 --> 00:02:48,810
and I don't have any nurses
to assist me.

32
00:02:49,410 --> 00:02:50,710
You have a nurse right here.

33
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:53,750
I have three years of experience,

34
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:56,380
including in the delivery room.
I can help.

35
00:03:02,550 --> 00:03:05,560
All right. Let's do it. Let's move.

36
00:03:27,110 --> 00:03:28,880
This is her first time giving birth,
so it could be tough.

37
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:32,150
Please take good care of my wife.

38
00:03:42,190 --> 00:03:43,190
Don't worry.

39
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:46,800
I promise you,
the mother and baby will be safe.

40
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:17,400
(Operating room)

41
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:19,330
(Restricted area, Delivery)

42
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:20,700
This is driving me crazy.

43
00:04:21,270 --> 00:04:23,640
Has the universe gone crazy,
or what?

44
00:04:24,140 --> 00:04:27,040
Death had its sights on Dan Hui,
but it snatched Myung Hui instead.

45
00:04:28,140 --> 00:04:29,970
That's just so wrong!

46
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:35,280
Please...

47
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:42,150
Can't you at least save the baby?
Please?

48
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,930
It's a healthy baby boy.

49
00:04:51,630 --> 00:04:53,870
It's a miracle, plain and simple.

50
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:59,070
Doctor,
your daughter is healthy too.

51
00:05:02,170 --> 00:05:03,540
Both babies...

52
00:05:03,810 --> 00:05:06,240
were born the same day,
at the exact same time.

53
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:25,560
Look, I get by on pure confidence,

54
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,930
but soothing a crying baby?

55
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,330
It's the one thing I'm terrible at.

56
00:05:28,330 --> 00:05:29,630
So please stop crying, all right?

57
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:30,700
I'll try my best.

58
00:05:35,470 --> 00:05:36,870
What's wrong?

59
00:05:43,110 --> 00:05:44,480
You know too, don't you?

60
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:49,090
You know you lost your mom
the moment you were born.

61
00:05:55,630 --> 00:05:57,960
Wait, why are you crying too?

62
00:05:57,960 --> 00:06:00,260
You're crying for your friend,
is that it?

63
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:03,200
You're making me want to cry too,
so please stop.

64
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:04,840
Somebody, help.

65
00:06:05,540 --> 00:06:07,970
Don't cry. Peekaboo!

66
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:32,430
What's wrong with being alone?

67
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:36,000
That's just how life is.
You're not 12 anymore.

68
00:06:37,340 --> 00:06:40,470
You can live perfectly fine
even if I die.

69
00:06:42,170 --> 00:06:43,570
I was wrong.

70
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,780
It was all my fault.

71
00:06:49,850 --> 00:06:51,120
So please...

72
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:54,250
just wake up.

73
00:06:56,850 --> 00:07:00,360
We never even got to see
each other smile.

74
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:06,260
You could never be truly happy
because of me.

75
00:07:08,470 --> 00:07:11,370
This is just so unfair.

76
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:21,450
No...

77
00:07:22,180 --> 00:07:23,820
Don't go.

78
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:27,150
You can't leave like this.

79
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:29,820
You won't even get to see your baby,

80
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:33,890
or hold him in your arms.

81
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:38,900
You'll keep suffering,
even on the other side.

82
00:07:41,070 --> 00:07:44,970
It's too painful this way.

83
00:07:48,110 --> 00:07:51,640
This is too heartbreaking.

84
00:07:52,310 --> 00:07:53,740
Myung Hui.

85
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:56,510
Myung Hui, don't go.

86
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:59,050
Please, don't go!

87
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:03,550
Myung Hui!

88
00:08:04,260 --> 00:08:06,290
- You're making it harder for her.
- Myung Hui!

89
00:08:07,290 --> 00:08:08,860
Let her go in peace.

90
00:08:08,930 --> 00:08:11,930
No! How can I...

91
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:15,500
How can I let her go? Myung Hui!

92
00:08:15,570 --> 00:08:17,800
Myung Hui...

93
00:08:20,910 --> 00:08:24,180
What do I do?

94
00:08:24,610 --> 00:08:25,910
Myung Hui!

95
00:08:54,670 --> 00:08:56,040
Hold on a second.

96
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,040
It looks like...

97
00:08:59,110 --> 00:09:01,480
she was murdered.

98
00:09:23,770 --> 00:09:25,040
You're so pathetic.

99
00:09:26,170 --> 00:09:27,740
How can you be okay?

100
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:29,310
We just...

101
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:31,640
took a life.

102
00:09:32,610 --> 00:09:34,610
We'll be fine in a few days.

103
00:09:35,350 --> 00:09:36,850
It was the same five years ago.

104
00:09:37,450 --> 00:09:38,580
What do you mean, five years ago?

105
00:09:41,890 --> 00:09:42,920
Jung Ran.

106
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:46,890
Were you the one who hurt
Munhwadang's CEO's daughter?

107
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:53,060
She was sickly
and would've died soon anyway.

108
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,230
I just sent her off a few years...

109
00:09:55,830 --> 00:09:57,670
No, a few months early.

110
00:10:01,410 --> 00:10:03,740
I never should have followed you
in there.

111
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:10,380
I should've come to my senses
and done all I could to stop you.

112
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,350
I have no regrets.

113
00:10:14,650 --> 00:10:16,850
Rather than rotting away
in this living nightmare...

114
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:19,390
and dying a meek old woman,

115
00:10:20,290 --> 00:10:24,500
I'd rather fight my way out
and face the consequences.

116
00:10:27,370 --> 00:10:29,300
What if we get caught?

117
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,540
He just lost the son
he'd been waiting for.

118
00:10:31,540 --> 00:10:33,270
Do you think Tae Ho
will just let it go?

119
00:10:33,570 --> 00:10:35,340
He'll bring in the cops
or handle it himself.

120
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:37,710
Either way,
he'll get to the bottom of this.

121
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:41,680
Do you think I'd do this
without a plan?

122
00:10:42,110 --> 00:10:46,650
Don't worry. I know someone
who can handle this without a trace.

123
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:01,730
I didn't notice in the emergency,

124
00:11:02,030 --> 00:11:03,430
but there are ligature marks.

125
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:08,240
It's evidence of excessive force.

126
00:11:09,540 --> 00:11:11,480
They're signs of strangulation.

127
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:14,450
Then Myung Hui really was...

128
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,350
But who...

129
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:18,550
Who on earth...

130
00:11:46,780 --> 00:11:48,010
It was them.

131
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:52,750
Is there anyone you suspect?

132
00:11:52,820 --> 00:11:55,750
We saw some suspicious people
in front of Myung Hui's house.

133
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:58,760
They might be the killers.

134
00:11:58,860 --> 00:12:01,830
If we have suspects,
we can definitely find the killer.

135
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:06,600
She left us
the most crucial piece of evidence.

136
00:12:08,230 --> 00:12:12,370
When she arrived at the hospital,
she had no external bleeding.

137
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,840
This bloodstain...

138
00:12:15,470 --> 00:12:17,070
must belong to the killer.

139
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,140
Also...

140
00:12:19,110 --> 00:12:21,250
the blood on this...

141
00:12:22,850 --> 00:12:24,580
most likely belongs
to the killer too.

142
00:12:28,190 --> 00:12:29,250
So that's why...

143
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:33,560
That's why...

144
00:12:35,030 --> 00:12:37,090
Myung Hui was holding onto this
until the very end.

145
00:12:46,170 --> 00:12:47,270
Where are you going?

146
00:12:48,340 --> 00:12:49,540
I'm going to find...

147
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:52,480
those people.

148
00:12:54,150 --> 00:12:55,210
I'll find them,

149
00:12:57,210 --> 00:12:58,620
and I will kill them.

150
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:02,450
Dan Hui!

151
00:13:03,190 --> 00:13:04,760
Dan Hui!

152
00:13:05,420 --> 00:13:07,190
- Dan Hui, wake up!
- Are you okay?

153
00:13:07,190 --> 00:13:08,490
Stay with me.

154
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:12,200
Dan Hui, wake up!
What's wrong? Dan Hui!

155
00:13:25,380 --> 00:13:26,410
Today's the day...

156
00:13:27,380 --> 00:13:30,110
you sign the deal
with Wooju Department Store, isn't it?

157
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:33,050
If you already know,
then don't get on my nerves.

158
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:36,690
I don't want you ruining my mood
before something this important.

159
00:13:36,950 --> 00:13:39,920
Then you'd better be prepared
to get upset.

160
00:13:41,990 --> 00:13:43,090
What are you talking about?

161
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:45,700
You...

162
00:13:46,230 --> 00:13:48,470
You have connections
with the police, right?

163
00:13:49,670 --> 00:13:50,830
The police? Why?

164
00:13:52,670 --> 00:13:54,810
Something came up
that needs to be taken care of.

165
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:56,940
I...

166
00:14:00,580 --> 00:14:01,580
I...

167
00:14:03,850 --> 00:14:05,320
I killed Kim Myung Hui.

168
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:11,020
If it gets out that I'm a murderer,

169
00:14:11,020 --> 00:14:13,120
your Wooju Department Store deal
is off.

170
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,460
You said
you wouldn't stop at jewelry...

171
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:17,730
and that you had bigger plans.

172
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,860
Will you let it fall apart
before it begins?

173
00:14:20,260 --> 00:14:22,730
On top of that,
my child is now your only heir.

174
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:25,070
It's not like...

175
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,270
you can kill me, right?

176
00:14:30,810 --> 00:14:32,580
So handling this quietly...

177
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,280
Are you saying...

178
00:14:36,850 --> 00:14:39,050
- Oh Jung Ran, you...
- Yes.

179
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:41,790
That's right! I killed her.

180
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:44,420
I'm done begging for your love.

181
00:14:44,420 --> 00:14:47,460
My child will be Adele's heir
and take over.

182
00:14:47,730 --> 00:14:49,330
That's all I'm living for now.

183
00:14:51,730 --> 00:14:54,030
Oh Jung Ran, you...

184
00:14:58,100 --> 00:15:00,240
If you help me just this once,

185
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:03,440
I'll do anything you ask,
and I'll put up with it all.

186
00:15:04,210 --> 00:15:06,080
Isn't protecting Adele
more important...

187
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,950
than putting me in prison?

188
00:15:08,580 --> 00:15:10,180
Aren't I more useful...

189
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:12,750
as your child's mother
than in the grave?

190
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:16,490
Aren't Adele
and your own ambition...

191
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:17,990
more important to you...

192
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:20,590
than that wretch Kim Myung Hui?

193
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:32,100
Move!

194
00:16:00,930 --> 00:16:03,400
Jung Ran, are you all right?

195
00:16:03,470 --> 00:16:06,600
You're going to be the death of me.

196
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:09,840
How could you ask Tae Ho
to clean up your mess?

197
00:16:12,310 --> 00:16:14,080
He would have found out
one way or another.

198
00:16:15,210 --> 00:16:17,780
It's better to use him
than to get caught later.

199
00:16:18,420 --> 00:16:21,120
Look at you. You're shaking.

200
00:16:22,590 --> 00:16:23,850
Instead of all this,

201
00:16:24,220 --> 00:16:26,220
just come away with me
to the countryside.

202
00:16:27,460 --> 00:16:30,130
We could just live quietly...

203
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:33,160
Shut it and go check on the villa.

204
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:36,830
See how Park Tae Ho handles things,

205
00:16:37,130 --> 00:16:39,870
and call me if anything happens. Go!

206
00:16:39,940 --> 00:16:41,970
Darn it. This is insane.

207
00:16:42,540 --> 00:16:43,740
Shoot!

208
00:16:50,180 --> 00:16:51,180
That's right.

209
00:16:52,450 --> 00:16:54,080
This will do it.

210
00:16:58,590 --> 00:17:00,320
Now, there's nothing...

211
00:17:01,660 --> 00:17:03,230
that can stand in our way.

212
00:17:18,540 --> 00:17:21,310
She had cancer surgery in Seoul
and was released yesterday.

213
00:17:21,980 --> 00:17:23,450
She was already pushing herself
as it was,

214
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:25,280
but with Myung Hui dying...

215
00:17:25,950 --> 00:17:27,890
What's worse,
Myung Hui was murdered.

216
00:17:28,690 --> 00:17:30,420
It would be weirder
if she were okay.

217
00:17:31,260 --> 00:17:33,220
There's a lot to take care of,

218
00:17:33,860 --> 00:17:36,290
so wouldn't contacting
the child's father help?

219
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:40,230
I think it's best
if Dan Hui does that herself.

220
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:44,030
Then let's do what we can to help.

221
00:17:44,330 --> 00:17:46,970
I'll report it to the police
and turn in any evidence.

222
00:17:47,370 --> 00:17:49,610
I'll get started
on the funeral arrangements.

223
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:52,340
First, I'll arrange for her body
to be transported.

224
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:54,280
Sure.

225
00:18:08,530 --> 00:18:11,960
Grandma, is that nurse a whale?

226
00:18:12,330 --> 00:18:13,700
Can she eat all that?

227
00:18:17,270 --> 00:18:19,200
It sure is a lot.

228
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:23,370
Well, when you need to eat,
especially after having a baby,

229
00:18:23,870 --> 00:18:26,310
it's better to have too much
than not enough.

230
00:18:28,580 --> 00:18:30,010
Package delivery.

231
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:42,060
No way. It's the one I wanted!

232
00:18:43,230 --> 00:18:44,360
Who could've sent this?

233
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:52,540
Grandma, who sent this present?

234
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:53,840
(Ma'am, I'm sorry I left
without a goodbye.)

235
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:56,240
It's from the nurse.

236
00:18:57,510 --> 00:18:59,340
She's going away for a while.

237
00:18:59,910 --> 00:19:02,880
She sent this so you'll be okay
until she gets back.

238
00:19:03,180 --> 00:19:04,310
Really?

239
00:19:04,980 --> 00:19:07,950
How many sleeps
until she comes back?

240
00:19:08,020 --> 00:19:09,120
That's a good question.

241
00:19:09,750 --> 00:19:11,490
I wonder how many sleeps it'll be.

242
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:41,990
Gosh, my legs are shaking so bad.

243
00:19:43,150 --> 00:19:45,790
It still feels creepy,
even in broad daylight.

244
00:19:49,990 --> 00:19:50,990
That's right.

245
00:19:51,430 --> 00:19:54,100
However you look at it,
I shouldn't have come back here.

246
00:19:56,570 --> 00:19:57,570
No, wait.

247
00:19:58,700 --> 00:20:01,200
If this all goes south,

248
00:20:01,270 --> 00:20:03,940
I'll be in deep trouble. Shoot.

249
00:20:32,670 --> 00:20:33,670
Who are you?

250
00:20:33,940 --> 00:20:35,240
What are you doing here?

251
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:38,740
This is the villa of Adele's owner,

252
00:20:38,740 --> 00:20:40,440
and his wife sent me...

253
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:43,110
His wife?

254
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:46,080
Are you the driver?

255
00:20:47,850 --> 00:20:48,850
Yes.

256
00:20:50,620 --> 00:20:52,960
What did you guys do
with Kim Myung Hui's body?

257
00:20:57,660 --> 00:21:01,670
I'm a cop sent by Mr. Park,
so you'd better start talking.

258
00:21:02,130 --> 00:21:04,670
How can I get rid of the body
that's not here?

259
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:07,800
Hold on,

260
00:21:08,610 --> 00:21:11,010
are you saying the body is gone?

261
00:21:14,010 --> 00:21:16,410
What? Didn't you guys handle it?

262
00:21:16,810 --> 00:21:17,810
No.

263
00:21:18,650 --> 00:21:19,650
Then what?

264
00:21:20,980 --> 00:21:22,850
Did the body just get up
and walk away?

265
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:24,120
No way...

266
00:21:26,190 --> 00:21:28,160
Did she turn into a ghost?

267
00:21:43,270 --> 00:21:46,010
Shoot. Darn it!

268
00:21:48,580 --> 00:21:50,280
Unbelievable!

269
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:57,120
What's up?

270
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:59,220
I just stepped out for a minute.

271
00:22:01,490 --> 00:22:02,490
What?

272
00:22:03,790 --> 00:22:06,130
You got a report
about a new mother dying?

273
00:22:08,470 --> 00:22:09,670
Kim Myung Hui?

274
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:15,840
(Baek OB-GYN)

275
00:22:21,950 --> 00:22:22,950
Seriously?

276
00:22:27,250 --> 00:22:28,790
Anyone here?

277
00:22:31,090 --> 00:22:32,090
Darn it.

278
00:22:33,120 --> 00:22:34,690
Give me a break...

279
00:22:51,740 --> 00:22:52,740
I'm with the police.

280
00:22:53,810 --> 00:22:57,550
We got a call
that you reported the death...

281
00:22:57,550 --> 00:22:59,320
of Kim Myung Hui.

282
00:22:59,950 --> 00:23:02,020
Oh, right. Yes, her.

283
00:23:02,350 --> 00:23:03,490
Where's the clinic director?

284
00:23:03,620 --> 00:23:06,360
He just stepped out to buy diapers.

285
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:07,490
He should be back soon.

286
00:23:07,860 --> 00:23:10,490
My husband is the director here.

287
00:23:11,330 --> 00:23:12,400
But...

288
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,070
why is this clinic so empty?

289
00:23:15,830 --> 00:23:17,430
It's kind of creepy.

290
00:23:17,530 --> 00:23:20,040
We're in the middle of closing.

291
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:22,210
We've already moved
most of our things out,

292
00:23:22,510 --> 00:23:23,540
but...

293
00:23:23,910 --> 00:23:26,310
my water broke unexpectedly
last night.

294
00:23:27,210 --> 00:23:29,750
He reopened it temporarily
just for me.

295
00:23:29,750 --> 00:23:31,850
Oh, I see.

296
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:36,090
Goodness me!

297
00:23:36,620 --> 00:23:39,390
Looks like you had twins.

298
00:23:39,990 --> 00:23:43,460
No, only this one's mine.

299
00:23:43,460 --> 00:23:44,590
The other one...

300
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:46,930
is hers.

301
00:23:47,430 --> 00:23:49,670
The mother who passed away
last night.

302
00:23:50,270 --> 00:23:51,640
It's so tragic.

303
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:53,700
She never even got to see
her baby's face...

304
00:23:53,770 --> 00:23:55,210
Hold on.

305
00:23:55,740 --> 00:23:56,740
Are you saying...

306
00:23:57,310 --> 00:23:59,140
that the late Kim Myung Hui...

307
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,340
gave birth to a child?

308
00:24:01,380 --> 00:24:04,650
Yes, my husband rushed her in
for an emergency C-section...

309
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:06,050
and saved the baby.

310
00:24:21,630 --> 00:24:22,630
Darn it.

311
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:25,340
- Give me that.
- Hey! What are you doing?

312
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:27,170
Hey! Get back here!

313
00:24:29,210 --> 00:24:30,210
What are you doing?

314
00:24:35,410 --> 00:24:37,510
Jung Ran needs to know first.

315
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:41,050
You darn punk!

316
00:24:41,690 --> 00:24:42,850
Seriously. Are you crazy?

317
00:24:42,950 --> 00:24:45,690
Jung Ran should know
about this first, so...

318
00:24:46,190 --> 00:24:48,060
Mr. Park needs to hear this first.

319
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:50,730
If you want this mess cleaned up,
stop interfering and get lost.

320
00:25:05,140 --> 00:25:06,140
Shoot.

321
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:09,750
(Intensive Care Unit)

322
00:25:24,830 --> 00:25:25,830
Darn it.

323
00:25:30,330 --> 00:25:32,770
Hey, stop right there!

324
00:25:37,910 --> 00:25:38,980
Dan Hui.

325
00:25:41,180 --> 00:25:43,650
Just now, that guy we suspect...

326
00:25:53,460 --> 00:25:55,590
(Adele and Wooju Department Store
Contract Signing Ceremony)

327
00:25:55,660 --> 00:25:57,590
- Did you enjoy your meal?
- Yes.

328
00:25:57,830 --> 00:25:59,060
- To a great partnership.
- Sure.

329
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:01,030
- I believe we're ready.
- Yes, of course.

330
00:26:17,580 --> 00:26:19,650
Goodness, I apologize.

331
00:26:20,550 --> 00:26:21,550
All right, then.

332
00:26:21,620 --> 00:26:23,050
(Partnership Agreement)

333
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:24,990
There. All set.

334
00:26:25,660 --> 00:26:27,060
(Adele and Wooju Department Store
Contract Signing Ceremony)

335
00:26:27,090 --> 00:26:28,730
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

336
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:31,130
I look forward to our partnership.

337
00:26:32,830 --> 00:26:34,760
Thank you, everyone.

338
00:26:37,470 --> 00:26:39,700
The person you have called
is unavailable.

339
00:26:39,770 --> 00:26:42,010
- This is ridiculous.
- Please try again later.

340
00:26:42,210 --> 00:26:44,410
He should at least pick up
when I'm cleaning up his mess.

341
00:26:48,380 --> 00:26:50,480
I swear, I saw the baby myself...

342
00:26:51,150 --> 00:26:52,820
I'm telling you, I know what I saw.

343
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:55,390
The baby's alive.

344
00:26:56,650 --> 00:26:58,790
What are we supposed to do?

345
00:26:59,790 --> 00:27:01,260
What else?

346
00:27:02,090 --> 00:27:03,530
Take the baby away right now.

347
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:05,860
Hurry, before Park Tae Ho
gets to him first!

348
00:27:17,770 --> 00:27:18,880
Freeze.

349
00:27:19,580 --> 00:27:21,980
You're waiting here
until I get in touch with Mr. Park.

350
00:27:25,550 --> 00:27:26,950
But...

351
00:27:27,150 --> 00:27:30,220
I really have to use the bathroom.
I can't wait.

352
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,060
Come on...

353
00:27:33,090 --> 00:27:34,760
Let go of me.

354
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,230
As if I'd fall for that.

355
00:27:37,930 --> 00:27:40,560
I'm serious. It's coming.

356
00:27:41,060 --> 00:27:43,000
- I've really got to go.
- Hey.

357
00:27:43,170 --> 00:27:45,340
- I'm...
- Number 1 or 2?

358
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:46,400
Should I go right here?

359
00:27:47,170 --> 00:27:48,170
You're faking it.

360
00:27:49,270 --> 00:27:50,270
Hey!

361
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:59,980
(Nursery)

362
00:28:11,030 --> 00:28:12,500
What the heck is going on?

363
00:28:13,500 --> 00:28:14,730
That's strange!

364
00:28:15,900 --> 00:28:17,400
I swear the baby was right here!

365
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:19,270
Are you a complete fool or what?

366
00:28:20,170 --> 00:28:21,170
Are you sure
this is the right place?

367
00:28:21,770 --> 00:28:23,740
- But...
- There's no one here.

368
00:28:24,270 --> 00:28:25,740
Kim Myung Hui's body
has disappeared as well.

369
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:28,410
How can a dead body vanish?

370
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:35,220
What in the world is going on?

371
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:59,580
- Honey, are you all right?
- Yes, I'm fine.

372
00:29:00,710 --> 00:29:02,950
I've safely moved your sister
into the car.

373
00:29:03,450 --> 00:29:04,450
Thank you.

374
00:29:06,420 --> 00:29:08,050
I'll go with her
to the funeral home.

375
00:29:08,320 --> 00:29:10,090
You go straight to our house, okay?

376
00:29:10,820 --> 00:29:13,020
- Be careful.
- Don't worry.

377
00:29:16,090 --> 00:29:17,730
We should get out of here too.

378
00:29:17,730 --> 00:29:18,900
Alright.

379
00:29:19,730 --> 00:29:20,730
Let's go.

380
00:29:23,430 --> 00:29:24,800
Find them now!

381
00:30:06,180 --> 00:30:09,110
(Pearl in Red)

382
00:30:09,380 --> 00:30:12,120
We have to find them
before Tae Ho's people do.

383
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:13,350
A hostage?

384
00:30:13,450 --> 00:30:15,150
If we take the baby hostage,

385
00:30:15,150 --> 00:30:17,890
we'll have leverage over him.

386
00:30:18,090 --> 00:30:19,260
This has gotten way out of hand.

387
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:20,720
This only got out of hand...

388
00:30:20,760 --> 00:30:23,930
because you were pathetic enough
to lose my son.

389
00:30:24,090 --> 00:30:26,130
Tae Ho will kill us.

390
00:30:26,130 --> 00:30:28,200
I'm doing this so I can stay alive.

391
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:29,670
Wait, was it them?

392
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:33,800
The wife of Adele's president
did all this.

393
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:35,410
Oh, no. Our poor Dan Hui!

394
00:30:35,410 --> 00:30:37,540
Where's my son?

395
00:30:41,180 --> 00:30:43,180
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
